# User-facing labels

House style for short UI chrome across VRMXT surfaces: Warudo `[Label]` / menus /
buttons / status, Blender `bl_label` / property `name` / panel text, materials-override
catalog `displayName`, and autocomplete display strings.

Does **not** apply to ShaderLab names, API identifiers, enum/serialized values,
file paths, or deslop of long-form docs.

## Casing

Use **sentence case**: capitalize the first word and proper nouns only.

| Do | Don't |
|----|--------|
| `Enable materials override` | `Enable Materials Override` |
| `Export file suffix` | `Export File Suffix` |
| `Add VFX emitter` | `Add VFX Emitter` |
| `Apply VRMXT override` | `Apply Vrmxt Override` |

Keep established product/brand casing: **VRMXT**, **Warudo**, **lilToon**,
**Poiyomi**, **MToon**, **UniVRM**, **Blender**. Acronyms stay uppercase
(VRM, GLB, URP, BIRP, VFX).

## Voice and length

- Prefer the fewest words that stay unambiguous.
- Buttons and operators: verb + object (`Apply shader overrides`, `Add common
  props`, `Clear VFX preview`).
- Trailing ellipsis (`…` or `...`) only when more input is required before the
  action completes.
- No trailing period on labels. No ALL CAPS. No emoji in labels.
- Help/description / `bl_description` may be full sentences; labels stay scannable.

## Identifier vs label

- ShaderLab / resolve keys stay exact (e.g. `.poiyomi/Poiyomi Toon`, `lilToon`).
- UI `displayName` / `[Label]` / `bl_label` may be friendlier (`Poiyomi Toon`,
  `lilToon`) but must not invent a second resolve string.
- One concept → one label wording across Warudo, Blender, and matching catalogs.
- **Upstream shader property labels:** materials-override catalog `displayName` for
  props we do not own (lilToon, Poiyomi, etc.) may match the upstream inspector /
  ShaderLab wording, including Title Case. Do not sentence-case those to “fix”
  this rule. This exemption does **not** apply to house chrome we author (Warudo
  `[Label]`, Blender `bl_label` / panel titles, operators, status).

## Churn

- Follow this rule for **new** labels and labels you already touch.
- Do not mass-rename existing Title Case labels unless the task asks for it.
